    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The Institute of Labor and Industrial Relations was founded in the Spring of 1957 under the joint auspices of the University of Michigan and Wayne State University. Its objective is to encourage practical education and research in all areas of industrial relations.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The Institute's records measure one linear foot and date from 1949 to 1975. They consist of a scattering of materials, arbitrarily arranged into a single topical file. Of most interest are the executive board records (1957-1960; 1966-1969) and a few unpublished papers regarding aspects of labor relations in Michigan.</p>
    </scopecontent>
